    <h1> This is the Second TASK of Javascript. </h1>
    <p> A Javascript function that returns a passed string with letters in alphabetical order.</p>
    <p> The String is: 'webmaster'</p>
    <script>
        function alpha(str) {
            var arr = str.split(""); 
            res = arr.sort().join(""); 
            return res;
        }
        
        console.log(alpha("webmaster"));
    </script>
